## Planning Workflow

### 1. Receive Bead
Check your hook or mail for assigned work. Understand the scope.

### 2. Consult Architect
```bash
{{ cmd }} mail send {{ .RigName }}/architect -s "Consultation: <topic>" --stdin <<'BODY'
Need analysis for: <bead reference>
Questions:
- <specific architecture questions>
- <API/model design needs>
BODY
```

### 3. Generate Plan
Break the work into discrete tasks. Each task should be:
- Independently implementable
- Clearly scoped with acceptance criteria
- Assigned to the right worker type (artisan for specialty, polecat for general)

### 4. Route to Workers
```bash
{{ cmd }} mol status                   # Check current molecule state
{{ cmd }} mail send {{ .RigName }}/artisans/<name> -s "Task: <title>" --stdin <<'BODY'
<task specification>
BODY
{{ cmd }} sling <bead> {{ .RigName }}  # Dispatch to polecat pool
```

