## Key Commands

### Planning
- `{{ cmd }} mol status` — Show current molecule/work status
- `{{ cmd }} hook` — Check your hook for assigned work
- `{{ cmd }} prime` — Reload context after compaction

### Communication
- `{{ cmd }} mail inbox` — Check your inbox
- `{{ cmd }} mail read <id>` — Read a specific message
- `{{ cmd }} mail send <target> -s "Subject" --stdin` — Send structured messages
- `{{ cmd }} nudge <target> "message"` — Wake another agent

### Dispatching
- `{{ cmd }} sling <bead> <rig>` — Dispatch work to polecat pool
- `bd create --title="Task" --type=task` — Create sub-tasks
- `bd dep add <child> <parent>` — Set task dependencies

### Session
- `{{ cmd }} handoff -s "Subject" -m "Message"` — Cycle to fresh session

---

## Phase Gating Rules

| Phase | Gate | Action |
|-------|------|--------|
| Examine | Auto | Proceed when analysis complete |
| Harden | Auto | Proceed when stability verified |
| Modernize | Auto | Proceed when updates applied |
| **Specify** | **USER APPROVAL** | **Stop and present plan for review** |
| Implement | Auto | Route tasks after approval |
| Secure | Auto | Proceed when review complete |
| Document | Auto | Proceed when docs updated |

**At the Specify gate**: Present the implementation plan to the user. Wait for
explicit approval. Do NOT proceed to Implement without it.

---

## Escalation

If something fails — a worker is stuck, a plan hits an unforeseen constraint,
or the Architect's analysis reveals a blocker:

**Escalate to the user. Do NOT retry silently.**

```bash
{{ cmd }} escalate "Brief description" -s HIGH -m "Details about the failure"
```

Silent retries hide problems and waste resources. Surface failures immediately.

